docs.title: useAnalytics
docs.description: Hook giving you access to the instance of @availity/analytics-core for manually tracking events, and changing different variables.

docs.title: App Icon
docs.description: A component which outputs one of the "App Icons" from Availity UI Kit

docs.title: <Favorites /> ( Default Export )
docs.description: The Provider Component that stores all of the user's favorites for use in the favorite components.

docs.title: <FavoriteHeart />
docs.description: The default Favorite Icon that can be used to store a favorited item. Can only be used inside of a `` Provider.

docs.title: <FeedbackForm />
docs.description: This is the underlying form, which is exposed in case you need to gather feedback inline.

docs.title: Page Header
docs.description: The standard Availity application header that appears at the top of the page. It can include an app icon, payer logo, and/or the feedback loop.

docs.title: <PaginationContent />
docs.description: This is the container of all the items rendered to the DOM when the Pagination provider receives items. Must be /nested inside a Pagination component.

docs.title: PaginationContext
docs.description: If you are using a class component, you can subscribe to the pagination by using this context.

docs.title: usePagination
docs.description: This is a custom hook for grabbing any Pagination Data you may need from the Pagination provider.

docs.title: <Pagination /> ( Default Export )
docs.description: This is the provider component needed for @availity/pagination components to work. All @availity/pagination components must be children of a Pagination provider.

docs.title: <AvResourcePagination />
docs.description: This is a wrapper around the Pagination Component that can be used for paginating @availity/api-axios resources.

docs.title: SpacesContext
docs.description: If you are using a class component, you can subscribe to the spaces by using this context.

docs.title: <SpacesGhostText />
docs.description: Display the ghost text for a given space. Renders null if the ghost text should not display.

docs.title: <Space /> ( Default Export )
docs.description: This is the provider component needed for @availity/spaces components to work. All @availity/spaces components must be children of a Spaces provider.

docs.title: useSpaces
docs.description: This is a custom hook for grabbing spaces from the Spaces provider.

docs.title: useSpacesContext
docs.description: If you are using a function component, you can subscribe to the spaces by using this hook.

docs.title: Training Link
docs.description: Provide a link for training videos for your app

docs.title: Contributing
docs.description: This is a monorepo managed using lerna in independent mode (each package is versioned and published individually).

docs.title: <Date /> ( Default Export )
docs.description: Date picker without a Label or Feedback

docs.title: <DateField />
docs.description: The same as FormikDate but with a Label that appears above input and a Feedback that appears below the input.

docs.title: <DateRange />
docs.description: A date range, consisting of 2 fields, a start date and an end date, without a Label or Feedback

docs.title: <DateRangeField />
docs.description: The same as DateRange but with a Label that appears above the input and a Feedback that appears below the input.

docs.title: <SelectField />
docs.description: The same as Select but with a Label that appears above the input and a Feedback that appears below the input.

docs.title: <FilePicker />
docs.description: The raw file picker which automatically resets the value of the input, allowing the same file to be selected multiple consecutive files.

docs.title: <Upload /> ( Default Export )
docs.description: The default export is an all-in-one solution which handles uploads, encrypted file password requests and file state management for you.
